---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Mauritius Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/mauritius/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Seychelles for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/seychelles' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'mauritiusFit', header: 'Mauritius Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR 14,000-20,000/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR 16,500-23,500/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR 13,000-18,500/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR 12,000-17,000/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Mauritius Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'MUR 3,000-8,000/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MUR 12,000-20,000', annual: 'MUR 144,000-240,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MUR 17,000-27,000', annual: 'MUR 204,000-324,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MUR 23,000-36,000', annual: 'MUR 276,000-432,000' },
  { category: 'Mauritius Public', monthly: 'Free for residents', annual: 'Limited services' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'MUR 1,500-4,000/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mauritius 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Mauritius. Tropical paradise, retirement visa, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mauritius"
  subheadline="Mauritius offers tropical island paradise, dedicated retirement visa, English/French bilingualism, and tax-efficient living—a premier retirement destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/mauritius-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Mauritius</h2>
  <p>
    Mauritius is a tropical paradise with substance—stable democracy, English and French widely spoken, diverse culture, and attractive retirement programs. The Premium Visa specifically targets retirees and remote workers. It's one of the most welcoming retirement destinations globally.
  </p>

  <p>
    Grand Baie offers resort-style living with restaurants and beaches. Port Louis provides urban energy as the capital. The East Coast has quieter beach communities. Black River/Tamarin attract nature lovers with mountains and lagoons. The entire island is accessible.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Adequate private; limited public</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English official; French/Creole widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MUR 60,000-150,000/month (~$1,400-3,500)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round (cyclone season Dec-Apr)</li>
      <li><strong>Visa:</strong> Premium Visa specifically for retirees</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> 15% flat rate; no capital gains; no inheritance tax</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Mauritius Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Mauritius has free public healthcare that's adequate for basic needs but limited for complex care. Private healthcare is better—clinics like Wellkin Hospital, Clinique Darné, and Apollo Bramwell provide good care with modern facilities. Many expats rely entirely on private healthcare.
  </p>

  <p>
    For serious conditions, evacuation to South Africa, India, or Europe may be necessary. Mauritius is an island—airlift is required for truly complex cases. International insurance with evacuation coverage is essential for seniors.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Island Healthcare Limitations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Mauritius is a small island (2,000 km²) with limited specialist capabilities. While private hospitals handle most needs, complex cardiac surgery, cancer treatment, or rare conditions may require evacuation to South Africa (4 hours) or India. Ensure international insurance includes medical evacuation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Mauritius actively welcomes retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Premium Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Specifically designed for retirees, remote workers, and those with passive income. Requires $1,500+/month income (pension, investments). Valid 10 years, renewable. No local income tax on foreign-sourced income. Very attractive for retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Occupation Permit (Retired Non-Citizen)</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees transferring $1,500+/month to Mauritius bank. Valid 10 years. Similar benefits to Premium Visa but older program structure.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Investment</h3>
  <p>
    Buying property $375,000+ in designated developments (IRS, RES, PDS) grants residence. Combines investment with retirement living.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Mauritius:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Premium Visa:</strong> Health insurance required for application</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage level:</strong> Must meet government minimum standards</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Essential given island limitations</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Best option for seniors (local limits apply)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Mauritius</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for Mauritius—local insurers have age limits and limited coverage. Ensure your plan includes: evacuation to South Africa/India, coverage at Mauritius private hospitals, and worldwide emergency coverage. Premium Visa requires proof of adequate health coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Mauritius, international coverage with evacuation is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Mauritius</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good African/Indian Ocean network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Good regional coverage, competitive pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Strong evacuation network to South Africa/India</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Mauritius retirement with evacuation included.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Mauritius are moderate:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local private care is affordable; high deductible for evacuations</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash locally:</strong> Private consultations MUR 1,500-3,000; easy cash</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Africa/Asia focused rather than worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Don't skimp on evacuation:</strong> This is essential island coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,500/month pension. Seeking tropical retirement with English.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Premium Visa. Cigna Global with UK coverage. Wellkin Hospital for local care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~MUR 17,000/month (~£320). Tropical lifestyle with excellent healthcare backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: French Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension €3,200/month. Francophone preferred. Buying property.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> PDS property purchase for residence. BUPA Global for both. French culture with tropical setting.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~MUR 40,000/month combined (~€850). Bilingual paradise lifestyle.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: South African, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring from Johannesburg. Seeking safer environment. ZAR 45,000/month pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Premium Visa. Now Health with SA evacuation coverage. Uses Apollo Bramwell locally.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~MUR 14,000/month (~ZAR 8,000). Safer, similar timezone, familiar medical network.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How welcoming is Mauritius to retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very welcoming. The Premium Visa was specifically designed to attract retirees and remote workers. Government actively promotes Mauritius as retirement destination. Process is straightforward. The island has long history of welcoming expats and diverse population (Indian, African, European, Chinese heritage).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about cyclone season?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cyclone season is December-April. Major cyclones are infrequent; warning systems are good. Buildings are constructed to withstand cyclones. Most cyclones pass without major damage. It's a consideration but not a deal-breaker. Many retirees travel during peak season anyway.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Mauritius expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate. Not as cheap as Southeast Asia but reasonable. Imported goods are expensive (island shipping costs). Local food is affordable. Housing varies—beachfront is expensive; inland is reasonable. A comfortable retirement is possible on $2,500-3,500/month including insurance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use English everywhere?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes. English is the official language; French is widely spoken. Creole is the everyday language for locals. All three work. Private healthcare operates in English/French. Government services are English. You won't have language barriers in Mauritius.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with evacuation coverage for Mauritius.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Mauritius Economic Development Board and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
